50|$|Christian {{tradition}} {{states that}} Erasmus of Formiae, {{also known as}} <b>Saint</b> <b>Elmo,</b> was finally executed by disembowelment in about A.D. 303, after he had suffered extreme forms of torture during the persecutions of Emperor Diocletian and Maximian.|$|R
50|$|In 1775, {{during the}} reign of Ximenes, an {{unsuccessful}} revolt known as the Rising of the Priests occurred in which Fort <b>Saint</b> <b>Elmo</b> and <b>Saint</b> James Cavalier were taken by rebels, but the revolt was eventually suppressed.|$|R
